There are  memory leaks in Call::GetUnMarshaler() and Call::GetMarshaler()
methods.
Code from mozilla/java/xpcom/connect/src/Call.cpp:
bcIMarshaler * Call::GetMarshaler() {
    out = new ostrstream();
    return new Marshaler(out);
}
In this code we always alloc the memory for "out" variable and 
do not free allocated for "out" in previous call.

Leak in GetMarhaler is similar, but for "in" variable.

For example due to leak in GetMarshaler method we
lost ~22kb only on startup with default test.

